Sorry, I really should have started a new thread to discuss this.  I'd also like to apologize for my message being directed toward you, Talinia.  My concern is not with you, its with this trend.<br>
<br>
I can't justify giving myself (or someone else) a bonus on a roll due to level.  If my friend Gilligan, for example, is on the raid with me, I could not roll with a bonus.  It would be the same with any other rogue.<br>
<br>
So, I can understand why you might need to use the bonus as 'honey' to attract higher level players for the run.  But that still seems like an insult to lower level players to me.  I just can't justify that anti-social action, so I will say right now all my rolls will be as a level 50 player, regardless of what other rogues do.  Or, me and the other rogue(s) may agree on something beforehand.<br>
<br>
So again, I apologize for the bitter tone of my posting.  It was due to my personal embarrasment felt whenever the loot rules are brought up.  I don't want people to think I would take that advantage myself, and I guess it just upsets me that people are so accepting of it.  Perhaps I would think differently if I was a member of a more popular class.<br>
<br>
-Snag <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/utalinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talinia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(10/13/00 10:33:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/dr_lag/tal.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Well Snag it is all a moot point anyway as I have nuked most of my rules, since the people I talked to about them couldn't agree if they were actually heping anything and were just needlessly complex.  The level bonus is gone as well since it failed to shift the mean level on runs.  I still will keep the accumulated run bonus though.  I believe if you go on enough runs you should get something eventually.<br>
<br>
It was never my intent to screw over lower level people like Gilligan, he's a great guy.  I'm sorry if it looked that way.  I do runs because people don't invite me on theirs usually, and want to give others the same chance.  I set the rules up the way they were previously because I thought they were best for the run as a whole.  I want my runs to succeed with minimal duration/deaths and to get drops for the denziens of test server.  That was the only reason I had the rules in the first place... not to be elitist or anti social.<br>
<br>
And, for whatever reason, there are no rogues on this run.  Bah!  No one likes fear.<br>
<br>
-Tal, who still hasn't won anything except on other people's runs, and isn't even very high level =P <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/utalinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Talinia</A> at: 10/13/00 10:52:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#292929><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub21.ezboard.com/usnagglepus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snag Glepus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#F0E68C>(10/13/00 11:26:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/feqtestregistryfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=18.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <br>
